AIM: 
To write a C program to evaluate the expression - LOG(x3+y3+z3) using library functions. 
 
 
ALGORITHM FOR INSERTION SORT:
1. Start the program. 
2. Declare variables x, y, z, and result as float or double. 
3. Read the values of x, y, and z from the user. 
4. Calculate x3, y3, and z3 using pow() function from <math.h>. 
5. Add them together. 
6. Use log() to compute the natural logarithm of the sum. 
7. Display the result. 
8. Stop the program. 
 
 
PROGRAM:
#include <stdio.h> 
#include <math.h> 
int main() { 
double x, y, z, result; 
printf("Enter value of x: "); 
scanf("%lf", &x); 
printf("Enter value of y: "); 
scanf("%lf", &y); 
printf("Enter value of z: "); 
scanf("%lf", &z); 
result = log(pow(x, 3) + pow(y, 3) + pow(z, 3)); 
printf("The value of log(x^3 + y^3 + z^3) = %.4lf\n", result); 
return 0; 
} 
 
 
